30
00:01:29.660 --> 00:01:31.803
You want to have all your paperwork in place.

31
00:01:31.803 --> 00:01:35.660
You want to have all your scores and weightings in place so you can

32
00:01:35.660 --> 00:01:39.160
show objectively that you treated everyone equally,

33
00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:40.660
as you should.

34
00:01:40.660 --> 00:01:40.993
Okay,

35
00:01:40.993 --> 00:01:44.327
now that you have someone selected and you've discussed and

36
00:01:44.327 --> 00:01:46.660
agreed who the best candidate would be,

37
00:01:46.660 --> 00:01:50.993
you want to complete whatever HR or company paperwork is required to move

38
00:01:50.993 --> 00:01:54.910
the processing forward for the particular new hire.

39
00:01:54.910 --> 00:02:01.660
Okay, now let's move on to the remaining paperwork.

40
00:02:01.660 --> 00:02:04.607
Okay, now on to the final paperwork.

